The new feature is the passages outside the car.
It's more just about the kind of interactive animation that Jack usually flees from someone and you have to help him do it by printing the right buttons in the right moments.
Nothing complicated.
But it is surprising that there are far fewer passages in the game than you would expect (specifically perhaps only three).
In the end, however, it is to the benefit of the cause, because this element has no chance of becoming annoying and, in the context of the above, thus ranks among the elements that make the game better.
The driving model is in the footsteps of previous episodes.
