A typical feature of Czechs' travel at this time was to carver, canned goods, salamis, etc. to save.
Another important moment was the introduction of a freely convergeable Czech crown, which our tourists were able to buy the Western currency freely after many of the years.
But our standard of living, and with it, average salaries rose, resulting in another important moment around 1997.
Thanks to the increased demand for travel, travel agents have started to regularly prepare tours with charter air links since 1997, making air tours incredibly cheaper thanks to the possibility of contracting quantity discounts compared to the past.
By the end of the 1990s, the Czechs already had visa-free travel to virtually every developed country in the world, except the US, which continued to facilitate our travel.
